<TITLE> Mysterious blast at BCIC HQ in Motijheel leaves 4 hurt </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 28 (bdnews24.com)A mysterious explosion that occurred on the second floor of BCIC headquarters in Motijheel in the city Monday morning left four people injured, police said. Sub-inspector Azizul Haque of Motijheel police station told bdnews24.com, "A loud explosion took place on the second floor of the BCIC head office at around 9 am today (Monday). The impact of the explosion tore parts of a window and threw it down across the road." "A fire also broke out on the same floor following the blast. Rescue operations are already on," he said. The fire brigade doused the blaze at around 10:45 am. They are now trying to contain the fire from spreading in the backside of the building. Abdur Rashid, deputy director of fire service, said, "Four injured persons were rescued and sent to the hospital. The fire on the second floor is now under control." But he couldn't say how the explosion occurred. Immediately after the explosion, RAB, police and fire service personnel arrived at the spot and took up position. People were also found thronging the scene. bdnews24.c
